    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Eastern form of Syriac script that remained in use in Central Asia and Siberia until the 13th or 14th century. It is seen on inscriptions on gravestones in southern Siberia.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
